social_posts.post_text: few and far between captured outfits of 22 🫶🏼
Everything is circular once again, connected, old and new
Sub zero BC serve over the winter

Presenting ASCENSION, designer @shirleytang__’s @parsons_fashion Thesis Collection. ASCENSION continues ORIENS’s exploration of Futurism, focusing within this collection the dichotomous yet circularly connective relationship between the Ancient and Future. 

This Thesis serves as both an expansion of the ORIENS world, and a meaningful return to the word’s roots and origins— the powerful, motion embedded visual of the sun rising from the eastern horizon, as subversion of its modern meanings by revisiting its origins, to imagine forwards and upwards in ways both unbounded yet tethered to its past and future. Grounding the Ancient within the designer’s own cultural heritage and reconnecting with rituals and sky bound mythology in Ancient Chinese culture, ASCENSION seeks to stake a space and world upon the glimmering horizon, a limbo that promises expansive opportunity for creation and storytelling.

Seeking from these myths that grip upon our imaginations and extend boundlessly past time, they now evolve as circular, at once of the past, of the future, of fleeting nowness. Women are transformed into deities and enchantresses in this new world, portals of power and sensuality. Obelisks, monuments, adorned and revered.

Thank you to the incredible team for making this dream come true, and to a beautiful, perfect, circular end to my BFA journey. To learning and new worlds.
